            . I am a <rs id="t18221204-72-viclabel390" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-72-victim696 t18221204-72-viclabel390"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18221204-72-crimeloc391">West-street, Limehouse</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18221204-72-crimeloc391" type="placeName" value="West-street, Limehouse"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18221204-72-crimeloc391" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-72-off388 t18221204-72-crimeloc391"></join>. The prisoner came to lodge with me on a Thursday, in April, and said he was chief mate of a ship, and on Monday, about half-past nine o'clock, he sent me to redeem a sextant for him - I left him alone sitting in the kitchen. I locked up all the other rooms, and returned about half-past eleven o'clock; I found the parlour door broken open, and every thing taken out of the drawers. I lost the articles stated in the indictment - the prisoner was gone; I did not see him again till he was in custody. I had the waistcoat to make from a slopseller.</p>
               <p>
            
