            . I am an officer. In consequence of information, I had the prisoner detained on this charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I admit taking the lodging, but deny taking any of the property, or pawning any part of it. I sent her to redeem a sextant and other things worth 8 l., which she has applied to her own use. Other persons were in the house at the time. The pawnbroker at first said he had no knowledge of me - he was told he must be positive, and then said I was the man.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 32.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18221204-72-verdict392" type="verdictDescription">
